Notes on getting gitian builds up and running using Docker:

These instructions distilled from:
  https://docs.docker.com/install/linux/docker-ce/ubuntu/
  https://docs.docker.com/docker-for-mac/install/
  
... see there for complete details.


Here's a description of eXtremal's setup on ubuntu 16.04 and 18.04:

1. Prepare root directory for build
2. git clone https://github.com/devrandom/gitian-builder.git
appy patch https://pastebin.com/AUtfxVsi

diff --git a/bin/make-base-vm b/bin/make-base-vm
index a0967ad..a636485 100755
--- a/bin/make-base-vm
+++ b/bin/make-base-vm
@@ -201,6 +201,7 @@ if [ $DOCKER = "1" ]; then
 FROM $base_image

 ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
+RUN rm /etc/apt/sources.list.d/ubuntu-esm-infra-trusty.list
 RUN echo 'Acquire::http { Proxy "$MIRROR_BASE"; };' > /etc/apt/apt.conf.d/50cacher
 RUN apt-get update && apt-get --no-install-recommends -y install $addpkg

3. git clone https://github.com/primecoin/primecoin -b primecoin-0.16.3
4. Obtain MacOSX10.11.sdk.tar.gz as described in README https://github.com/primecoin/primecoin/blob/primecoin-0.16.3/doc/README_osx.md
MacOSX10.11.sdk.tar.gz needs to be put in gitian-builder/inputs/
5. Install docker https://docs.docker.com/install
6, sudo apt-get install apt-cacher-ng
6. Create VM (run from gitian-builder root directory): bin/make-base-vm --suite trusty --arch amd64 --docker
7. Build primecoin (run from root build directory): primecoin/contrib/gitian-build.sh --build -c -j 8 -m 11000 eXtremal primecoin-0.16.3
  Where is:
    -j N: Parallel build using N threads
    -m M: Memory limit in megabytes